commitResults.messageTitle: Add user greet and firewell message
Build a skeletal version of Duke
commitResults.messageBody:
Split the procedure of Duke into getRawCommand(), parseCommand(String),
and runCommand(String[]).

It makes the skeleton version of Duke easier to understand, and
easier to maintain in the future (like a command line tool).

commitResults.messageTitle: Add funciton Add and List and other utilities
commitResults.messageBody:
Command parser parseCommand(String) can now recognize string in quotes.
Duke might support shell-like command in the future.

commitResults.messageTitle: Separate the function into more specific classes and managers
commitResults.messageBody: Some extra functions have been added (for example, multi-argument command line).
